description: The SPDR S&P Global Dividend ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return of the S&P Global Dividend Aristocrats Index (the “Index”)Seeks to offer exposure to high dividend yielding global firms that follow a managed-dividends policy of having increasing or stable dividends for at least ten consecutive yearsThe Index includes the top 100 qualified stocks with highest indicated dividend yield, with no more than 20 stocks selected from each country and 35 stocks from each GICS sectorThe weight of each Index constituent is capped at 3%, and no single country or GICS sector can be more than 25% of the Index
name: SPDR S&P Global Dividend ETF
